Protocol.text: PCR products were dried in 384 well plates (Genetix)and resuspended in 20ul of 50%DMSO/0.3xSSC. These were arrayed onto GAPS-II slides (Corning) by a Microgrid II robot (Biorobotics). Slides were then baked at 80C for 2 hours.

Reporter.name: RNA pol III subunit RPC II

Description.text: This array contains PCR products which were amplified from European flounder (Platichthys flesus) genomic DNA, liver or ovary cDNA and clones derived from SSH (Clontech PCR-select) comparisons of wild flounder from the Tyne estuary (Tyne and Wear, UK) and Alde estuary (Suffolk, UK). This array includes PCR products representative of genes of toxicological interest.
